eNCA's Pule Letshwiti-Jones has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The 72-hour activation period to find Hillary Gardee's killers ends on Friday. Police Minister Bheki Cele set the deadline for arrests to be made. READ: Police launch 72-hour activation to find Gardee's killer The 28-year-old's body was found at a timber plantation outside Mbombela in Mpumalanga on Tuesday. She was killed execution-style. Hillary is the daughter of attorney and former EFF Secretary-General, Godrich Gardee.